      "writtenOn": "2018-06-25T19:41:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That doesn\u0027t quite work because chunks can\u0027t be processed twice, and regexes can\u0027t span chunks. That results in:\n\n* \"Bug: \"\n* HTML(\"\u003ca ...\u003ehttps://crbug.com/1234\u003c/a\u003e\")\n* \", 5678\"\n\nAs a result, the BUG regex no longer captures the whole line, just the \"empty\" first chunk.\n\nTBH, no one would write it this way anyway, but, as I was writing unit tests, it seemed weird to have \"Bug: 123, https://crbug.com/456\" work but not \"Bug: https://crbug.com/456, 123\". So I went ahead and made it fully work.",
